# The error occurred again because I mistakenly used a string to refer to the stone furnace instead of the appropriate entity object.
# 
# I need to retrieve the stone furnace entity again and then insert the iron ore into it.

stone_furnace = get_entities({Prototype.StoneFurnace}, position=Position(x=-7.0, y=7.0))[0]  # Retrieve the stone furnace entity.
insert_item(Prototype.IronOre, target=stone_furnace, quantity=10)  # Inserting 10 iron ore into the stone furnace.
print(f"Inventory changed to {inspect_inventory()}")
print(f"Entities on the map: {get_entities()}")
